org.tms.api

Interface TableElement

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BaseElement, Listenable, Taggable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Cell, Column, Derivable, Row, Subset, Table, TableRowColumnElement

    public interface TableElement
extends BaseElement, Listenable, Taggable
    Methods common to all TableElements, including Tables, Rows, Columns, Subsets, and Cells.

    Since:
    "1.0"
    Version:
    "1.1"

      • setLabel

        void setLabel(String label)
        Set the label string to associate with this TableElement. Set the label string to null to remove the existing label, if one exists. Label strings can be used in Derivation expressions to refer to this or other TableElements. For example, if a Column's label is set to the string "Units", and that column contains numeric values, then the following Derivation expression is valid: 
            mean(col "Units") * 10.50
        This expression could be used to set a Cell value to the average cost of inventory per site.
        Parameters:
        label - the new label string

      • isLabelIndexed

        boolean isLabelIndexed()
        Returns true if this TableElements labels are indexed. When indexed, label strings must be unique within the set of items indexed. For example, if Row labels in a Table are indexed, then the Row labels in that table must all be different.
        Returns:
        Returns true if this TableElements labels are indexed
